# HeadHunter — Job Search Co-pilot

You are operating in the HeadHunter job-search plugin repo. All data lives in `data/*.json`. All operations go through the Node scripts in `scripts/`. **Never edit `data/*.json` by hand** — use `crud.js`.

## Data operations

```bash
node scripts/crud.js list applications          # show all applications
node scripts/crud.js list interviews            # show all interviews
node scripts/crud.js list tasks                 # show all tasks
node scripts/crud.js add applications '{"company":"Acme","role":"SWE","status":"Applied","priority":"High"}'
node scripts/crud.js update applications <id> '{"status":"Technical"}'
node scripts/crud.js move <appId> "Technical"  # forward-only pipeline move
node scripts/crud.js complete-task <taskId>
node scripts/crud.js seed                       # load 5 demo applications (first run)
```

Entities: `applications`, `interviews`, `tasks`, `contacts`, `notes`.

## Pipeline stages (forward-only)
`Saved → Applied → Phone Screen → Technical → Onsite → Offer → Accepted`
Terminal (from any stage): `Rejected`, `Declined`, `Ghosted`

## Views and analytics

```bash
node scripts/dashboard.js           # metrics table
node scripts/dashboard.js --json    # raw JSON metrics
node scripts/analytics.js           # funnel with conversion rates
node scripts/calendar.js            # interview agenda
node scripts/timeline.js <appId>    # per-application timeline
node scripts/session-briefing.js    # pipeline + overdue + stale briefing
```

## Candidate profile

```bash
node scripts/candidate-profile.js show
node scripts/candidate-profile.js set '{"personal":{"name":"..."},"salary":{"target_base_ils":50000}}'
node scripts/candidate-profile.js extract-cv <file.txt>
```

## Job scanning and scoring

```bash
node scripts/score-job.js <job-metadata.json>   # deterministic pre-score vs candidate profile
```

Scoring fields: `match_score` (0–100, skills/exp/location/salary), `success_score` (0–100, qualification fit + company selectivity + competition).

## CV and applications

```bash
node scripts/generate-cv-html.js --input <cv.md> --out <cv.html>   # A4 HTML → open in browser → Cmd+P → PDF
```

## Follow-ups and reminders

```bash
node scripts/draft-followups.js                 # detect stale/silence/offer-deadline scenarios
node scripts/send-stale-reminders.js --dry-run  # preview stale-app digest
```

## Integrations (always use --dry-run first)

```bash
node scripts/sync-notion.js --dry-run           # preview Notion sync
node scripts/sync-todoist.js --dry-run          # preview Todoist sync
node scripts/sync-google-calendar.js --dry-run  # preview Calendar sync
node scripts/sync-google-tasks.js --dry-run     # preview Google Tasks sync
node scripts/sync-twilio.js --dry-run           # preview WhatsApp digest
```

## Backup

```bash
node scripts/backup.js                          # timestamped JSON snapshot → data/backups/
node scripts/restore.js <backup.json> --confirm # restore from snapshot
```

## Import/Export

```bash
node scripts/csv-import.js <file.csv>           # dry-run (print parsed rows)
node scripts/csv-import.js <file.csv> --write   # import into applications.json
node scripts/csv-import.js --url <url> --write  # import from remote CSV URL
node scripts/export-applications.js --format csv --out ./export.csv
node scripts/export-applications.js --format json --out ./export.json
```

## Settings

Edit `settings.json` to change defaults. Key: `headhunter`.

```json
{
  "headhunter": {
    "defaultCurrency": "USD",
    "staleThresholdDays": 7,
    "research": { "studyWeeks": 4, "hoursPerWeek": 10 }
  }
}
```

## Key data model fields (JobApplication)

`id`, `company`, `role`, `status`, `priority`, `applied_date`, `source`, `location`, `remote_type`, `salary_min`, `salary_max`, `currency`, `job_url`, `match_score`, `success_score`, `scanner_notes`, `research_dir`, `research_status`, `tailored_cv_path`, `cover_letter_path`, `referral_contact_id`

Full schema: `references/data-model.md`

## Testing

```bash
bash scripts/test.sh    # 17 self-tests — run after any change to verify nothing broke
```
